records.addlTxt:
Defendant Michael A Quella in court with attorney Frederick F Klimetz.  Timothy Suha appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Plea Colloquy.

Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 3.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Counts 1 and 2 are dismissed and read in.

The Court Orders the Following:

Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:

 30 Days Huber (Credit - 0 days) HUBER WITH STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS.

Term of Probation:  12 months

Conditions of Probation:
- Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
- No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
- No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
- Any valid prescription drugs must be taken in the manner in which they are prescribed;
- Inform agent of all prescriptions;
- Sign Medical Release for Agent;
- Perform  20 hours of community service within the first 10 months of probation;
-Operate a Motor Vehicle with a Valid Drivers License.

Costs: $243.00 
DNA Surcharge:  $200.00
(To be paid as a condition of probation at the rate of $75.00  per month commencing 6-1-15).

Expunction is conditionally granted upon completion of sentence, payment of all costs/fees and no new criminal law violations pending or outstanding.  Defendant must Petition the Court in writing upon successful completion of the sentence.
